TITLE: Using Default OpenAPI Hook with Hono
DESCRIPTION: Example of using Stoker's default OpenAPI hook with Hono for handling validation errors. This hook provides standardized error responses for Zod validation failures with a 422 status code.
SOURCE: https://github.com/w3cj/stoker/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_5

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { OpenAPIHono } from "@hono/zod-openapi";

import defaultHook from "stoker/openapi/default-hook";

/*
Any validation errors will respond with status code 422 and body:
{
  success: false,
  error: {}, // Full Zod Error
}
*/
const app = new OpenAPIHono({
  defaultHook,
});

export default app;
```

