TITLE: Creating oneOf Schema Array for OpenAPI
DESCRIPTION: Example of using Stoker's oneOf helper to generate schema objects for OpenAPI. This is used internally by jsonContentOneOf but can be used directly for custom schema definitions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/w3cj/stoker/blob/main/README.md#2025-04-22_snippet_9

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { z } from "@hono/zod-openapi";

import oneOf from "stoker/openapi/helpers/one-of";
import createErrorSchema from "stoker/openapi/schemas/create-error-schema";
import IdParamsSchema from "stoker/openapi/schemas/id-params";

const bodySchema = z.object({
  name: z.string(),
});

/*
* Returns: SchemaObject[]
*/
const result = oneOf([createErrorSchema(IdParamsSchema), createErrorSchema(bodySchema)]);
```

